To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the New York Freedom of Information Law, I hereby request the following records:

Documents for the period January 1, 2018 through present that reflect receipt of any payments by funeral homes or funeral providers to the New York State Department of Law / Office of the Attorney General (or to any New York State fund through OAG) in connection with:

• the “Funeral Rule Offenders Program” (FROP);
• enforcement or compliance activity relating to the FTC “Funeral Rule” / “Funeral Industry Practices Rule”;
• any “voluntary payment” in lieu of civil penalties associated with the Funeral Rule; and/or
• any payments described as “0.8%” of average annual gross sales in connection with Funeral Rule compliance.

This request includes, but is not limited to, records maintained by OAG’s finance/accounting functions such as: cash receipts journals, deposit logs, check logs, accounts receivable/collections logs, payment transmittal logs, or equivalent accounting system exports.

For each responsive receipt/transaction, I request fields sufficient to identify:
• payer name (business entity) and payer city/state;
• amount;
• date received and date deposited;
• any description/memo field associated with the receipt;
• fund and revenue classification codes (or equivalent accounting classifications);
• any internal matter/case identifier if it already appears on the receipt record.

To reduce any privacy or security concerns, I do not request bank account numbers, routing numbers, personal identifiers, or consumer complainant information. Please redact only exempt portions and release all reasonably segregable portions.

If responsive records exist in a machine-readable format (CSV/XLSX), please produce them in that format.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Akash Mehta
